Cell.Text: Who are you?
<<Shared>> Name's Valdr. I hunt out of Falkreath.
What are you doing out here?

[S] <<Shared>> We tracked a bear to this den. Good coin for those pelts. We had the big sow cornered when they showed up. Three of them, out of nowhere. | Spriggans. Niels went down choking before we even knew to run. Ari died just inside. I never even thought the things were real.
Why are you still here?
[S] <<Shared>> I may have lost a drop or two of blood. Truth is, I'm not going anywhere like this. Hurts to breathe.
I may have a potion to spare.
[S] I just need a little to get going.
[S] <<Shared>> Much better. Thanks, friend. I wouldn't have lasted much longer without that.
<<Shared>> But now what? I can't just walk away. Not with my friends' bodies in there, being torn apart by those beasts.
I understand. Let me help you.
[S] G|You'd do that for a stranger? I don't know what to say. Lead on, I suppose.
Don't be foolish. I'll do it.
[S] G|You'd really risk your life for a stranger's honor? I don't even know what to say. Thank you, my friend. I'll wait here.
I may know a spell that would work...
G|Thank you. Please hurry!
I'll be back.
G|Please, I need help! I don't want to die on this damned log!
Greetings.
Thank Kynareth for you, stranger. I'd almost given up hope of walking away from here.
[S] Ari gave me this dagger when we first started hunting together. Always said it brought her luck. You should be the one to carry it now.
[S] G|<<Shared>> I'll give them a proper burial, then head back. Find me if you're ever in Falkreath. You'll always be welcome at my door.
Hello
[S] Changed your mind? Well, I can't give up so easily. I'm heading back.
[S] <<Shared>> Much better. Thanks, friend. I wouldn't have lasted much longer without that.
It's over.
[S] It's done, then. Justice, if you can call it that. | Look, I want you to have this. I know it isn't much, but it's important to me.
